!!!LVM needs activation
sudo vgscan
sudo vgchange -ay

How to Add a Directory to $PATH
Temporarily (for current shell session only)
export PATH=$PATH:/new/directory/path
Example: export PATH=$PATH:/home/axruffin/scripts

Permanently (survives reboot / new terminal sessions)
nano ~/.bashrc
export PATH=$PATH:/home/axruffin/scripts
source ~/.bashrc

Find the device
sudo fdisk -l

See logical volumes
lsblk -f

see if the kernel detected
dmesg --follow
dmesg | grep -i sd
dmesg | tail -n 50

Create a mount point
sudo mkdir /mnt/mydrive

Mount the filesystem
sudo mount -t ext4 /dev/sdb1 /mnt/mydrive

Unmount when done
sudo umount /mnt/mydrive

View mounted filesystems
df -ha

Confirm drive is visible at USB level
lsusb

[ -d /sys/firmware/efi ] && echo "UEFI boot" || echo "Legacy BIOS boot"

